Welcome back John!

Find the perfect tutor for you.

{/*SECTION 4*/} {/* About the App */}

About Us

We are a "by the students for the students" organization with the mission of helping student through their difficult classes when they have no where else to look. We use students who have taken certain classes or are experienced in certain subjects to help their fellow peers not fall behind.

Struggling with Coursework?

Reach out to our variety of tutors and your fellow students versed in a wide range of subjects. They are all willing to use their experience from the same classes you are struggling with to help you through your rough patch and understand any material you are struggling with. Each of our tutors are rated by the students they have tutored with a bio, and their areas of expertise listed as well. No need to stress about not knowing who to ask for help- Sign up now and choose from one of our many tutors based on subject, availability, and ratings.

{/* Text after About Us */}

Tutors available now.

Below is a list of tutors available now and a little bit about them.

{/*List of tutors */} {/* 1st tutor */}

Isabelle Wright

About Me: Hi! I am a Junior at The University of Texas at Dallas. I am currently majoring in Biology. I am from Austin, Texas. I am passionate about helping to protect endangered animals and my favorite artist is Taylor Swift. In my free time, I like to play soccer. My tutoring expertise include: Biology 101, Biology 102, Biochemistry 101, and Biochemistry 102. I enjoyed taking many of these courses at UTD and I look forward to tutoring you and helping you succeed.

Times available:

Monday, Wednesday @ 1-3PM

{/* 2nd tutor */}

Chris Lee

About Me: Hi! I am a Senior at the University of Texas at Dallas. I am currently majoring in Computer Science. I am from Portland, Oregon. I enjoy playing video games in my free time. I had a pretty cool internship this past summer at Google. My tutoring expertise include: Computer Science 101, Computer Science 102, Data Structures, and Operating Systems. Additionally, I am also available to teach multiple math courses including Calculus 1, Calculus 2, and Linear Algebra. I look forward to working with yall!

Times available:

Monday, Thursday @ 1-3PM

{/* 3rd tutor */}

Yash Gupta

About Me: Hi! I am a Junior at the University of Texas at Dallas. I am currently double majoring in Physics and Applied Mathematics. I am from Houston, Texas. I enjoy playing with my dog and building computers in my free time. My tutoring expertise include: Physics 1, Physics 2, Statistics, Multivariable Calculus, Linear Algebra, Discrete Mathematics 1, Discrete Mathematics 2, and Digital Logic. Can’t wait to teach yall!

Times available:

Monday, Thursday @ 1-3PM

{/* 4th tutor */}

Sarah Brown

About Me: Hi! I am a Senior at the University of Texas at Dallas. I am currently majoring in History with a minor in English. I am from Plano, Texas. I play for the UTD Women’s Volleyball team. I also enjoy running marathons in my free time. I am also very involved in the Kappa Alpha Theta Sorority on campus. My tutoring expertise include English 101, English 102, US History 101, US History 102, Literature, Language and Composition, Creative Writing, and Texas History.

Times available:

Monday, Thursday @ 1-3PM
